{"title_page": "Swimming at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 200 metre freestyle", "text_new": "{{use mdy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Women's 200 metre freestyle\n|games = 1984 Summer\n|image =\n|caption =\n|venue = [[McDonald's Olympic Swim Stadium]]\n|date = 30 July 1984 (heats & final)\n|competitors = 38\n|nations = 26\n|gold = [[Mary Wayte]]\n|goldNOC = USA\n|silver = [[Cynthia Woodhead]]\n|silverNOC = USA\n|bronze = [[Annemarie Verstappen]]\n|bronzeNOC = NED\n|win_value = 1:59.23\n|prev = [[Swimming at the 1980 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 200 metre freestyle|1980]]\n|next = [[Swimming at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 200 metre freestyle|1988]]\n}}\n{{SwimmingAt1984SummerOlympics}}\nThe final of the '''women's 200 metre freestyle''' event at the [[1984 Summer Olympics]] was held in the [[McDonald's Olympic Swim Stadium]] in [[Los Angeles, California]], on July 30, 1984.<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1984/SWI/womens-200-metres-freestyle.html |title=Swimming at the 1984 Los Angeles Summer Games: Women's 200 metres Freestyle |accessdate=March 5, 2017 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>\n\n==Records==\nPrior to this competition, the existing world and Olympic records were as follows.\n\n{{World Olympic Record\n| world_athlete   = {{flagathlete|[[Kristin Otto]]|GDR}}\n| world_mark      = 1:57.75\n| world_place     = [[Magdeburg]], [[East Germany]]\n| world_date      = 23 May 1984\n| world_ref       = \n| olympic_athlete = {{flagIOCathlete|[[Barbara Krause]]|GDR|1980 Summer}}\n| olympic_mark    = 1:58.33\n| olympic_place   = [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| olympic_date    = 24 July 1980\n| olympic_ref     = \n}}\n\n==Results==\n\n===Heats===\nRule: The eight fastest swimmers advance to final A (Q), while the next eight to final B (q).<ref>{{cite web|title=Los Angeles 1984: Swimming \u2013 Women's 200m Freestyle Heats|url=http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/