en's 200 metre freestyle|1988]]\n}}\n{{SwimmingAt1984SummerOlympics}}\nThe final of the '''women's 200 metre freestyle''' event at the [[1984 Summer Olympics]] was held in the [[McDonald's Olympic Swim Stadium]] in [[Los Angeles, California]], on July 30, 1984.<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1984/SWI/womens-200-metres-freestyle.html |title=Swimming at the 1984 Los Angeles Summer Games: Women's 200 metres Freestyle |accessdate=March 5, 2017 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref> The fastest eight qualified for the final, the next eight for the B-final.\n\n==Records==\nPrior to this competition, the existing world and Olympic records were as follows.\n\n{{World Olympic Record\n| world_athlete   = {{flagathlete|[[Kristin Otto]]|GDR}}\n| world_mark      = 1:57.75\n| world_place     = [[Magdeburg]], [[East Germany]]\n| world_date      = 23 May 1984\n| world_ref       = \n| olympic_athlete = {{flagIOCathlete|[[Barbara Krause]]|GDR|1980 Summer}}\n| olympic_mark    = 1:58.33\n| olympic_place   = [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| olympic_date    = 24 July 1980\n| olympic_ref     = \n}}\n\n==Results==\n\n===Heats===\nRule: The eight fastest swimmers advance to final A (Q), while the next eight to final B (q).<ref>{{cite web|title=Los Angeles 1984: Swimming \u2013 Women's 200m Freestyle Heats|url=http://library.la84.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1984/1984v2.pdf|work=[[Los Angeles 1984]]|publisher=[[LA84 Foundation]]|pages=492\u2013493|format=[[PDF]]|accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Rank !! Heat !! Lane !! Name !! Nationality !! Time !! Notes\n|-bgcolor=#cfc\n| 1 || 3 || 4 ||align=left| [[Mary Wayte]] ||align=left| {{flagIOC|USA|1984 Summer}} || 2:00.69 || Q\n|-bgcolor=#cfc\n| 2 || 4 || 4 ||align=left| [[Cynthia Woodhead]] ||align=left| {{flagIOC|USA|1984 Summer}} || 2:00.85 || Q\n|-bgcolor=#cfc\n| 3 || 5 || 4 ||align=left| [[June Croft]] ||align=left| {{flagIOC|GBR|1