m/track/drowning-feat-laura-v-radio-edit/1801569 |title=Armin Van Buuren releases a progressive house single \"Drowning\" for the Mirage album |publisher=Beatport.com |date=2014-01-20 |accessdate=2015-11-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117015615/https://pro.beatport.com/track/drowning-feat-laura-v-radio-edit/1801569 |archivedate=17 November 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>|[[electro house]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pro.beatport.com/track/another-you-feat-mr-probz-extended-mix/7244664 |title=Armin Van Buuren releases a electro house single \"Another You\" for the Embrace album|publisher=Beatport.com|date=2014-01-20 |accessdate=2015-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://pro.beatport.com/track/ping-pong-original-mix/5330637 |title=Armin Van Buuren releases a electro house single \"Ping Pong\" |publisher=Beatport.com|date=2014-01-20 |accessdate=2015-11-07}}</ref>|[[big room house]]|[[dance-pop]]|[[psytrance]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://djmag.com/content/armin-drops-brand-new-psy-trance-track-%E2%80%98blah-blah-blah%E2%80%99-listen |title=Armin Drops Brand New Psy-trance Track, 'Blah Blah Blah': Listen |date=18 May 2018 |website=[[DJ Mag]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180520074315/https://djmag.com/content/armin-drops-brand-new-psy-trance-track-%E2%80%98blah-blah-blah%E2%80%99-listen |archive-date=20 May 2018 |accessdate=21 May 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|DJ|record producer|remixer}}\n| instrument       = {{hlist|[[Synthesizer]]|[[drum machine]]}}\n| years_active     = 1996\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Armada Music|Armada]]|A State of Trance|Armind|[[Kontor Records|Kontor]]|[[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]]|[[Sony Music|SME]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Gaia (band)|Gaia]]|Rising Star|[[Perpetuous Dreamer]]|Alibi}}\n| website          = {{URL|arminvanbuuren.com}}\n{{Infobox person\n| child            = yes\n| signature        = Armin van Buuren autograph.svg\n}}}}\n'''Armin Jozef Jacobus Dani\u00ebl van Buuren''' {{post-nominals|post-noms=[[Order of Orange-Nassau|OON]]}} ({{IPAc-en|v|\u00e6|n|_|\u02c8|b|j|\u028a\u0259r|\u0259|n}} {{respell|van|_|BEWR|\u0259n}},<ref>Van Buuren's own pronunciation that can be heard on ''A State of Trance''.</ref> {{IPA-nl|\u02c8\u0251rm\u026an \u02c8jo\u02d0z\u0259f j\u0251\u02c8ko\u02d0b\u028fs \u02c8da\u02d0ni\u02ccj\u025bl v\u0251n \u02c8by\u02d0r\u0259(n)|lang}}; born 25 December 1976)<ref name=\"armadaartistpg\" /> is a Dutch DJ, record producer and remixer from [[Leiden]]. Since 2001, he has hosted ''[[A State of Trance]]'' (ASOT), a weekly radio show, which is broadcast to nearly 40&nbsp;million listeners in 84 countries on over 100 FM radio stations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/about/|title=About \u2013 A State of Trance|accessdate=19 May 2016}}</ref> According to ''DJs And Festivals'', \"the radio show propelled him to stardom and helped cultivate an interest in trance music around the world.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.djsandfestivals.com/2015/armin-van-buuren-to-make-ims-asia-pacific-debut/|title=Armin van Buuren to make IMS Asia-Pacific debut -|date=2015-12-07|website=www.djsandfestivals.com|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812043428/http://www.djsandfestivals.com/2015/armin-van-buuren-to-make-ims-asia-pacific-debut/|archivedate=12 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nVan Buuren has won a number of accolades. He has been ranked the number one DJ by ''[[DJ Mag]]'' a record of five times, four years in a row.<ref>{{cite web|title=17 Armada DJs in DJ Mag Top 100. Though\u2013 Armin is No. 1 again!|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2012/10/17-armada-djs-in-dj-mag-top-100-armin-is-1-again/|accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref> He was ranked fourth on the ''DJ Mag'' Top 100 DJs list in 2015, 2016, and 2019,<ref>{{cite web |title=top 100 DJs 2019 |url=https://djmag.com/top100djs |website=djmag.com |accessdate=15 November 2019}}</ref> and third in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://djmag.com/top100dj|title=Top 100 DJs {{!}} DJMag.com|website=djmag.com|access-date=2017-06-01}}</ref> In 2014, he was nominated for a [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording]] for his single \"[[This Is What It Feels Like]]\" featuring [[Trevor Guthrie]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5819883/grammy-awards-2014-full-nominations-list-complete-nominees|title=Grammy Awards 2014: Full Nominations List|website=Billboard|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> which makes him the fourth trance artist ever to receive a [[Grammy Award]] nomination.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.djmastercourse.com/famous-progressive-trance-djs/|title=The Most Famous Progressive Trance DJs Of All Time|date=2015-03-02|website=DJ Master Course|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821024001/https://www.djmastercourse.com/famous-progressive-trance-djs/|archivedate=21 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In the United States, he holds the record for most entries, twenty-one, on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Dance/Electronic Albums]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|last=Murray|first=Gordon|title=Armin van Buuren Sets Record on Dance/Electronic Albums Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/code/5869512/armin-van-buuren-sets-record-on-dance-electronic-albums-chart|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=24 May 2014|date=10 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nArmin van Buuren was born in [[Leiden]], on 25 December 1976,<ref name=\"armadaartistpg\" /> but grew up in [[Koudekerk aan den Rijn]]. Van Buuren started making music when he was 14.<ref name=\"Interview with Armin van Buuren\">{{cite web|url=http://dancemusic.about.com/cs/interviews/a/IntAVBuuren.htm|title=Interview with Armin van Buuren|publisher=About.com|accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref> He was inspired by French electronic music composer [[Jean-Michel Jarre]].<ref name=\"Interview with Armin van Buuren\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.synthtopia.com/content/2009/05/29/armin-van-buuren-fanboy/|title=Armin van Buuren, Fanboy|last=|first=|date=|website=synthopia|publisher=|access-date=|accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref> Van Buuren graduated from the [[Stedelijk Gymnasium Leiden]] in 1995, and studied law at [[Leiden University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nextshark.com/armin-van-buuren-interview/|title=How a Simple Law Student Became an EDM Legend|date=2015-06-16|website=NextShark|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> He began working as a DJ in Club Nexus, playing multiple sets a week, most of which lasted six or more hours.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.beatport.com/en/focus-on-the-netherlands-armin-van-buuren/|title=Focus on the Netherlands: Armin Van Buuren|date=2010-10-08|website=Beatport News (EN)|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 1999, he met Dave Lewis who introduced him as a DJ in England and the United States.<ref name=\":1\" /> As his musical career began to take off, he put his law degree on hold, but he did return to graduate from law school in 2003.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://legacy.lawstreetmedia.com/schools/9-celebrities-didnt-know-law-degrees/|title=7 Celebrities You Didn't Know Had Law Degrees - Law Street (TM)|date=2015-07-15|website=Law Street (TM)|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2009, Van Buuren married Erika van Thiel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.exqlusiv.com/8-pictures-of-djs-with-their-girlfriend-wife-part-2/|title=8 pictures of DJs with their girlfriend / wife [Part 2]|date=2015-08-08|website=exQlusiv.com|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> Their daughter Fenna was born in July 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/armin-van-buuren-puts-mansion-miami-into-a-state-of-trance-on-june-2-6441028|title=Armin van Buuren Puts Mansion Miami Into A State of Trance on June 2|last=Gonzalez|first=Victor|date=2012-05-21|website=Miami New Times|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> Van Buuren announced just hours before he was due to headline the main stage at [[Tomorrowland (festival)|Tomorrowland]] (27 July 2013) that his wife had given birth to a son, Remy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/list/5166011/top-6-tomorrowland-moments-you-can-watch-right-now|title=Top 6 Tomorrowland Moments You Can Watch Right Now|website=Billboard|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 February 2018, Van Buuren explored his family history in an episode of the TV series ''Verborgen verleden'', the Dutch version of the UK series ''[[Who Do You Think You Are? (UK TV series)|Who Do You Think You Are?]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ntr.nl/Verborgen-Verleden/77/detail/Armin-van-Buuren/VPWON_1280993 |title=Armin van Buuren |language=Dutch |website=[[Omroep NTR|NTR]] |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===1996\u20131999: Early career and success===\nIn 1996, Van Buuren released ''EP'' and ''Push'' on Timeless Records. Van Buuren had his first success with a track called \"Blue Fear\", which was released under the Cyber Records label in 1997. Another successful track, \"Communication\", was released under the same label and became popular in [[Ibiza]], Spain in the summer of 1999.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.magneticmag.com/2015/05/armin-van-buuren-bio/|title=Armin van Buuren Bio|last=Editorial|first=Magnetic|date=5 May 2015|website=Magnetic Magazine|publisher=|access-date=21 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160713061945/http://www.magneticmag.com/2015/05/armin-van-buuren-bio/|archive-date=13 July 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> After being signed to [[AM PM Records]],<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/store/music/artist/armin-van-buuren/47780200-0200-11db-89ca-0019b92a3933/bio?display=grid|title=Armin Van Buuren Bio|last=|first=|date=|website=microsoft.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> this track entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] at No.&nbsp;18 in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/3672/armin/?Day=&Month=&Year=1963|title=ARMIN {{!}} full Official Chart History {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\n\nIn the beginning of 1999, Van Buuren started his label Armind together with United Recordings. The first release, Gig \u2013 \"One\", was well received. The second release, \"Touch Me\" under the name Rising Star, was signed to [[Ministry of Sound]] in the UK, before the record was released. By the time of his third release, Gimmick \u2013 \"Free\" was signed to [[R&S Records]]. During this year, he remixed the first two singles of [[Gouryella]] (''Gouryella'' and ''Walhalla'') and, under the guise of Rising Star, produced a remix of ''L'Esperanza'', a song by [[Airscape]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ferrycorsten.com/news/ferry-corsten-announces-gouryella-live|title=From the studio to the stage: Ferry Corsten announces Gouryella live!|publisher=[[Flashover Recordings]]|date=2 December 2015|accessdate=8 February 2017|author=Flashover Recordings|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912040028/http://ferrycorsten.com/news/ferry-corsten-announces-gouryella-live|archive-date=12 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/music/airscape-lesperanza-armin-van-buurens-rising-star-mix/ |title=Airscape - L'Esperanza (Armin Van Buuren's Rising Star Mix) |authorlink=Armada Music |website=[[Armada Music]] |access-date=8 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n===2000\u20132004: ''76'' and ''A State of Trance'' series===\nIn 2000, Van Buuren started his own Armin van Buuren compilation series, a mix of [[progressive house]] and [[vocal trance]] styles of music.<!-- according to who? --> His first compilation album, ''A State of Trance'' (not to be confused with his weekly ''[[A State of Trance]]'' radio shows), sold 10,000 copies<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gazettereview.com/2016/04/richest-djs-world/|title=The Top 10 Richest DJs in the World - The Gazette Review|last=Deml|first=Jessica|date=2016-04-09|website=The Gazette Review|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> and contains Van Buuren's remix of [[Moogwai]], \"Viola\". Teaming up with [[Ti\u00ebsto]], two new projects were born: Major League \u2013 \"Wonder Where You Are?\" was released on [[Black Hole Recordings]] and Alibi \u2013 \"Eternity\" was released on Armind. \"Eternity\" received club and chart success and was signed to [[Paul van Dyk]]'s imprint [[Vandit Records]]. Another major collaboration followed this. Together with [[Ferry Corsten]], Van Buuren recorded a [[riff]] titled \"Exhale<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2006/11/907/|title=Armin van Buuren - 10 Years - Order now! - Armada Music|date=2006-11-06|website=Armada Music|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\" for the System F album, ''[[Out of the Blue (Ferry Corsten album)|Out of the Blue]]''. Released as a single, this track reached Gold status.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ultramusic.com/artist/ferry-corsten/|title=Ferry Corsten / Ultra Music / Ultra Records / Ultra|website=Ultra Music / Ultra Records / Ultra|access-date=2016-06-21|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503043754/http://ultramusic.com/artist/ferry-corsten/|archivedate=3 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Under the pseudonym [[Gaia (Armin van Buuren alias)|Gaia]] he released \"4 Elements\" on Captivating Sounds, a sub-label of [[Warner Brothers]].<ref>http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/music/gaia-4-elements/</ref>\n\nHis second album, ''Basic Instinct'' featured a new track: \"Perpetuous Dreamer\" \u2013 \"The Sound of Goodbye\". This track entered the Dutch charts in June 2001 at number 26. Later in the year, the track hit No.&nbsp;1 on the [[Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Music/Club Play]] chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ellesdegraaf.net/elles_bio.html|title=Elles de Graaf {{!}} Biography|last=Krogull|first=Andreas|website=www.ellesdegraaf.net|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> The third album, ''In Motion'' was released 6 August 2001. A fourth album, ''Transparence'', followed in 2002. In 2003, he worked with such artists such as DJ Seth Alan Fannin throughout a global tour on Dance Revolution in Europe, selling out to crowds of 20,000 people in the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://themusicessentials.com/artist-of-the-month-february-2015-armin-van-buuren/|title=King Of Trance: Our Artist Of The Month For February 2015, Armin van Buuren! {{!}} T.H.E - Music Essentials|date=2015-02-02|website=T.H.E - Music Essentials|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820150227/http://themusicessentials.com/artist-of-the-month-february-2015-armin-van-buuren|archive-date=20 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2001, Van Buuren started his own radio show on [[ID&T]] Radio<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2006/05/803/|title=A State of Trance celebrates its 250th broadcast! - Armada Music|date=2006-05-10|website=Armada Music|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> (traditionally broadcast in Dutch and later English since ASOT 183). In this weekly two-hour show, entitled ''[[A State of Trance]]'', he plays the latest popular trance music tracks, and publishes the artists and track titles on his website. When ID&T Radio changed genres in 2004, Van Buuren moved ''A State of Trance'' to [[Fresh FM (Netherlands)|Fresh FM]] and later [[SLAM!FM]], two Dutch radio stations. It is now a weekly feature on [[Radio 538]], the Dutch radio station,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.538.nl/programma/37/a-state-of-trance|title=A State Of Trance|website=538.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> [[DI.FM]], an online radio station,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.di.fm/shows/a-state-of-trance|title=A State Of Trance with Armin van Buuren|website=Digitally Imported|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> and on [[XM Satellite Radio]], [[Electric Area|channel 52]] in the United States and Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.siriusxm.com/electricarea/weeklyschedule|title=Weekly Schedule - Electric Area|website=SiriusXM|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> A complete list of stations that broadcast ''A State of Trance'' can be found at the ASOT section of Armin's website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/stations/|title=Radio stations broadcasting A State of Trance|website=A State of Trance|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, he had a residency at Glow in Washington D.C.,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.clubglow.com/djs/armin-in-dc-a-14-year-old-journey/|title=Armin van Buuren + Glow Washington DC \u2013 A 14 Year Old Journey|website=Club Glow Washington DC|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> and played across North America. He regularly appeared at [[Amnesia (nightclub)|Amnesia]] on the island of [[Ibiza]], Balearic Islands, Spain. In October that year, Van Buuren was voted number 5 in the ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''.\n\nIn June 2003, Van Buuren celebrated the 100th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Bloomingdale, [[Bloemendaal aan Zee]], Netherlands and released his debut studio album, ''[[76 (album)|76]]'', a 76-minute album divided into 13 tracks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/discography/?release=Arma056|title=Armin van Buuren \u2013 76 \u2013 Release|accessdate=10 January 2012}}</ref> In the same year he was voted No. 3 in the ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]'' and held third place for the next two years (2004, 2005). Also in 2004, Van Buuren remixed the ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]'' theme song into a trance hit.\n\n===2005\u20132006: ''Shivers''===\n[[File:Armin van Buuren 2005 (cropped).jpg|thumb|240px|Armin van Buuren at [[Sensation (event)|Sensation White]] 2005]]\n\nOn 2 June 2005, he celebrated the 200th episode of ''[[A State of Trance]]'' at the [[Museumplein]] of [[Amsterdam]]. On 8 August 2005, Van Buuren released his second studio album, ''[[Shivers (album)|Shivers]]''. On the album Van Buuren worked with artists such as Pakistani-American singer [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]], English singer [[Justine Suissa]] and American trance duo [[Gabriel & Dresden]]. On 25 May 2006, he celebrated with various artists the 250th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Asta, [[The Hague]], Netherlands. He was voted number two in the 2006 ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''. On 17 May 2007, he celebrated with various artists the 300th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Pettelaarse Schans, [['s-Hertogenbosch]], Netherlands.\n\n===2007\u20132009: ''Imagine''===\nVan Buuren was elected best DJ in the world in the 2007 ''[[DJ Mag]]'' edition. On 12 January 2008, Van Buuren was given the \"Buma Cultuur Pop Award,\" the most prestigious Dutch music award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.armadamusic.com/news/pop-award-goes-to-armin-van-buuren|title=Pop Award goes to Armin van Buuren|last=|first=|date=|website=Armada Music|publisher=|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-06}}</ref> On 17 April 2008, Van Buuren released his third studio album, ''[[Imagine (Armin van Buuren album)|Imagine]]''. It features collaboration with singers such as [[Jacqueline Govaert]] of [[Krezip]]. The album debuted at number one on the [[MegaCharts|Dutch Albums Chart]]. The second single released from the album, [[In and Out of Love (Armin van Buuren song)|\"In and Out of Love\"]], featuring [[Sharon den Adel]] from the band [[Within Temptation]], has spawned a music video that has been viewed over 212 million times on YouTube.<ref name=\"YouTube\">{{cite web|author=Armada Music|author-link=Armada Music|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TxvpctgU_s8|title=Armin van Buuren ft. Sharon den Adel \u2013 In and Out of Love (Official Music Video)|publisher=YouTube|date=6 August 2008|accessdate=14 July 2012}}</ref> Since the release of ''Imagine'', Van Buuren has been working with [[Benno de Goeij]] of [[Rank 1]] on solo productions and remixes.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}} On 1 May 2008, he celebrated with various artists the 350th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Noxx, [[Antwerp]], Belgium. He was voted No. 1 in the 2008 ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]'' again.\n\nHe collaborated with his brother, guitarist Eller van Buuren, at [[Together as One (festival)|Together As One]] in Los Angeles, U.S., on New Year's Eve 2009, as well as on Armin's 2008 studio album ''[[Imagine (Armin van Buuren album)|Imagine]]''. His performance with his brother at Together As One was also the last event of his ''Armin Only: Imagine'' world tour. To celebrate the 400th episode of ''A State of Trance'', he performed at three shows with various artists in April, 2009 at Club Butan, [[Wuppertal]], Germany, [[AIR (nightclub)|AIR]], Birmingham, United Kingdom and Maassilo, [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]].\n\nAlso in 2009, Foreign Media Games announced the production of ''[[Armin van Buuren: In the Mix]]'', a [[music video game]] being produced in collaboration with Cloud 9 Music and Van Buuren's Armada Music label. The title was released on 12 November 2010 exclusively for the [[Wii|Wii console]].<ref>[http://worthplaying.com/article/2009/10/30/news/69826/ 'In The Mix: Featuring Armin van Buuren' (Wii) Shows Off Career Mode \u2013 Screen], 30 October 2009.</ref> He was voted number one DJ in the 2009 ''[[DJ Mag]]'' for the third consecutive year.\n\n===2010\u20132012: ''Mirage'' and appointment to the Order of Orange-Nassau===\nOn 3 March 2010, Van Buuren was awarded with the [[Golden Harp]] for his musical work and contribution to Dutch music, by [[Buma/Stemra]] at the 2010 Buma Harpen Gala in [[Hilversum]], Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bumacultuur.nl/nl/nieuws/171/buma-gouden-en-zilveren-harpen-buma-exportprijs-en-beste-nederlandse-lied-uitgereikt|title=Buma Gouden \u2013 en Zilveren Harpen, Buma Exportprijs en Beste Nederlandse Lied uitgereikt|date=3 March 2010|publisher=[[BUMA/STEMRA|Buma Cultuur]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=25 March 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100420102925/http://www.bumacultuur.nl/nl/nieuws/171/buma-gouden-en-zilveren-harpen-buma-exportprijs-en-beste-nederlandse-lied-uitgereikt|archivedate=20 April 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2010/03/armin-van-buuren-awarded-with-gouden-harp/|title=Armin van Buuren awarded with Gouden Harp|date=4 March 2010|publisher=[[Armada Music]]|accessdate=25 March 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100408055756/http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2010/03/armin-van-buuren-awarded-with-gouden-harp/| archivedate= 8 April 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> To celebrate the 450th episode of ''A State of Trance'', he performed with various artists at five shows across two continents. The locations were: [[The Guvernment]], Toronto, Canada on 1 April 2010, [[Roseland Ballroom]], New York City on 2 April and on 3 April again, Expo Arena, [[Bratislava]], Slovakia on 9 April and [[Centennial Hall]], [[Wroclaw]], Poland on 24 April.\n\nOn 23 June 2010, it was announced that Van Buuren's fourth studio album, ''[[Mirage (Armin van Buuren album)|Mirage]]'' was due to be released on 10 September.<ref>{{cite web|title=New single Full Focus available tonight at 00:00 |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/362/ |publisher=arminvanbuuren.com |date=23 June 2010 |accessdate=23 June 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100626060738/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/362/ |archivedate=26 June 2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> The first single \"Full Focus\", was released through [[iTunes Store]] on 24 June.<ref>{{cite web|title=New single Full Focus out now! \" Armin van Buuren|url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/06/new-single-full-focus-out-now/|publisher=arminvanbuuren.com|accessdate=10 July 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203195326/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/06/new-single-full-focus-out-now/|archivedate=3 December 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The song peaked at number 60 in the Netherlands. One of the confirmed tracks from the album is a collaboration with English singer [[Sophie Ellis-Bextor]] called \"[[Not Giving Up on Love]]\", which was released as a single from Bextor's fourth studio album, ''[[Make a Scene]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Nick|title=Music \u2013 News \u2013 Ellis-Bextor switches single plans|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a223927/ellis-bextor-switches-single-plans.html|date=7 June 2010|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=10 July 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100610213419/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a223927/ellis-bextor-switches-single-plans.html| archivedate= 10 June 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Nick|title=Armin werkte 'harder dan ooit' aan nieuwe plaat|url=http://www.depers.nl/entertainment/489763/Armin-werkte-harder-dan-ooit.html|language=Dutch|date=24 June 2010|publisher=DePers.nl|accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> Armin also wrote a song for English singer [[Seal (musician)|Seal]], but due to the release of his greatest hits album, ''[[Hits (Seal album)|Hits]]'', the collaboration never came together.<ref>{{cite web|last=van Luling|first=Dennis|title=Armin van Buuren verovert ook Zuid-Amerika|url=http://www.nu.nl/muziek/2281427/armin-van-buuren-verovert-zuid-amerika.html|language=Dutch|date=30 June 2010|publisher=[[NU.nl]]|accessdate=10 July 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100703135813/http://www.nu.nl/muziek/2281427/armin-van-buuren-verovert-zuid-amerika.html| archivedate= 3 July 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> On 12 September 2010, Van Buuren launched \"A State of Sundays\", a new weekly 24-hour radio show aired on Sirius XM Radio.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/09/armin-launches-a-state-of-sundays-on-sirius-xm/ |title=Armin launches A State of Sundays on Sirius XM \" Armin van Buuren |publisher=Arminvanbuuren.com |accessdate=2012-08-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120817032235/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/09/armin-launches-a-state-of-sundays-on-sirius-xm/ |archivedate=17 August 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> On 20 October 2010, Van Buuren won the award for Most Popular International DJ presented by The Golden Gnomes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldengnomeawards.com/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100917193926/http://www.goldengnomeawards.com/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2010-09-17 |title=Golden Gnome Awards |publisher=Golden Gnome Awards |accessdate=2012-08-30 }}</ref> A week later he was announced, for the fourth year running, as the number one DJ in ''[[DJ Mag]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/10/armin-van-buuren-no-1-dj-in-the-dj-mag-top-100-again/ |title=Armin van Buuren no 1 DJ in the DJ Mag Top 100 again! \" Armin van Buuren |publisher=Arminvanbuuren.com |accessdate=2012-08-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030015708/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/10/armin-van-buuren-no-1-dj-in-the-dj-mag-top-100-again/ |archivedate=30 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe 2010 edition of ''[[Armin Only]]: Mirage'' kicked off in November 2010, in [[Utrecht, Netherlands]], and was followed by shows in [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Kiev]], Buenos Aires, [[Melbourne]], [[Beirut]], [[Pozna\u0144]], Moscow and [[Bratislava]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminonly.com/shows-tickets/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100627145226/http://www.arminonly.com/shows-tickets/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2010-06-27 |title=Shows & Tickets \" Armin Only |publisher=Arminonly.com |accessdate=2012-08-30 }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Armin on air.jpg|thumb|240px|right|Van Buuren broadcasting the milestone 500th episode of his ''[[A State of Trance]]'' show at the official pre-party, live from Club Trinity in [[Cape Town]] on 17 March 2011.]]\nIn March and April, 2011, celebrating the 500th episode of his radio show, Van Buuren performed five live shows along with various artists; the first was in [[Johannesburg]], South Africa at MTN Expo Centre, and the second in [[Miami]]'s [[Ultra Music Festival]]. He then performed in [[Argentina]] at [[Estadio G.E.B.A.|GEBA]] in Buenos Aires, followed by a large event at Brabanthallen in [[Den Bosch]], Netherlands which included more than 30 DJs from countries all over the world and was attended by over 30,000 people. The final show was held in Sydney on 16 April at [[Acer Arena]]. In 2011, Van Buuren was appointed Officer of the [[Order of Oranje-Nassau]] for services to Dutch dance and music economy.<ref name=\"officer\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.armadamusic.com/news/armin-named-officer-in-the-order-of-oranje-nassau |title=Armin named Officer in the Order of Oranje-Nassau! |authorlink=Armada Music |website=Armada Music |publication-date=30 April 2011 |access-date=10 August 2017}}</ref> That year he also received the [[Key to the City|Key]] to ([[Freedom of the City|Freedom]]) of [[Leiden]] from the City Mayor, as well as being voted No. 2 in the 2011 ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''.\n\nTo celebrate the 550th episode of ''A State of Trance'', he performed with various artists on two different continents during fourth weeks. The show was called ''A State of Trance 550: Invasion''. The first event was celebrated at [[Ministry of Sound]] in London on 1 March 2012. On 7 March, Moscow held the second event at [[Expocentre]]. [[Kiev]]'s show was performed at International Exhibition Centre on 10 March. On 17 March, as part of the [[Beyond Wonderland]] festival in Los Angeles and on 25 March at the [[Ultra Music Festival]] in Miami. On 31 March, the biggest and final edition of ASOT 550 took place in the Brabanthallen of [[Den Bosch]], Netherlands. On 19 October 2012, Van Buuren was announced for a fifth non-consecutive year as the world's number one DJ according to ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2012/10/armin-van-buuren-back-to-number-one-in-dj-mag-top-100/ |title=Armin van Buuren back to number no one in DJ Mag Top 100! \" Armin van Buuren |publisher=Arminvanbuuren.com |date= |accessdate=20 October 2012}}</ref>\n\nTo celebrate the 600th episode of ''A State of Trance'', Van Buuren announced that he would perform with various artists all around the world in early 2014. The show was called ''A State of Trance 600: The Expedition''. It was announced that the show would tour the world, including stops in [[Madrid]], [[Mexico City]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Minsk]], [[Sofia]], [[Beirut]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Mumbai]], [[Miami]], [[Guatemala City]], [[New York City]], and [[Den Bosch]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/a-state-of-trance-600 |title=A State of Trance 600 \" A State of Trance |publisher=Astateoftrance.com |date= |accessdate=2013-07-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ASOT 650 New Horizons 2014 dates announced, tour will be 'massive,' says Armin van Buuren|url=http://www.dancingastronaut.com/2013/10/asot-650-new-horizons-2014-dates-announced-tour-will-be-massive-says-armin-van-buuren/}}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''Intense''===\nThe first single of Van Buuren's fifth studio album, ''[[Intense]]'', titled \"[[This Is What It Feels Like]]\", featured Canadian singer and songwriter [[Trevor Guthrie]], and was released on 5 April 2013. The single nominated for a [[Grammy Award]] for Best Dance Recording.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newson6.com/story/21641513/1-dj-armin-van-buuren-releases-1st-single-this-is-what-it-feels-like-from-his-5th-artist-album-intense-anaarmada-north-america-april-5th |title=#1 DJ Armin van Buuren Releases 1st Single \"This Is What It Feels Like\" from His 5th Artist Album 'INTENSE' (ANA/ARMADA NORTH AMERICA) April 5th \u2013 NewsOn6.com \u2013 Tulsa, OK |publisher=NewsOn6.com |accessdate=2013-07-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411130254/http://www.newson6.com/story/21641513/1-dj-armin-van-buuren-releases-1st-single-this-is-what-it-feels-like-from-his-5th-artist-album-intense-anaarmada-north-america-april-5th |archivedate=11 April 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The tour for the album, ''[[Armin Only]]: Intense'', was announced on 17 October 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminonly.com/news-item-details-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101201334/http://www.arminonly.com/news-item-details-19 |url-status=dead |archive-date=1 November 2013 |title=20 Dates and 19 Destinations for Armin Only Intense |publisher=Armin van Buuren |date=17 October 2013 |accessdate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>\n\n30 April 2013 saw the abdication of Queen [[Beatrix of the Netherlands]] in favor of her son, King [[Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands]], who was crowned that day. Van Buuren was the headline act in a performance to a live audience celebrating the King's crowning in Amsterdam. While he was performing live together with the [[Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra]], King [[Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands|Willem-Alexander]], Queen [[Queen M\u00e1xima of the Netherlands|M\u00e1xima]] and their three daughters made an unplanned visit on stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GeVvRGkXTLc |title=Armin van Buuren & The Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra perform for new Dutch king Willem-Alexander |publisher=Armada Music |date=19 May 2013 |accessdate=2013-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.demorgen.be/dm/nl/15698/Willem-Alexander/article/detail/1624976/2013/05/01/Uitstapje-koningspaar-stond-niet-in-draaiboeken.dhtml |title='Uitstapje' koningspaar stond niet in draaiboeken ('pleasure-trip' of royal couple was not part of plan of action) |publisher=De Morgen |date=1 May 2013 |accessdate=2013-12-30}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 October 2013, Armin van Buuren was ranked number two DJ in the world by ''[[DJ Mag]]''. On 26 January 2014, Armin van Buuren attended the [[56th Annual Grammy Awards|56th Grammy Awards]], in relation to his Grammy Award nomination for the single featuring Trevor Guthrie, \"This Is What It Feels Like\" in the category of [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording|Best Dance Recording]].\n\n===2015\u20132018: ''Embrace''===\n[[File:Armin van Buuren logo.svg|thumb|240px|Van Buuren's DJ logo, used in shows as of 2015]]\nOn 8 May 2015, Armin van Buuren released the first single from his sixth studio album, ''[[Embrace (Armin van Buuren album)|Embrace]]'', which was released on 29 October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/news/armin-van-buuren-announces-new-artist-album-embrace/|title=Armin van Buuren announces new artist album|publisher=}}</ref> The single is titled \"[[Another You (Armin van Buuren song)|Another You]]\" featuring [[Mr Probz]]. Three weeks after releasing \"Another You\", Van Buuren also debuted another remix from ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' official theme which is originally made by composer [[Ramin Djawadi]].<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Matt|last=Medved|date=8 June 2015|title='Game of Thrones' Theme Receives Trance Remix By Armin van Buuren|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/6590616/game-of-thrones-theme-armin-van-buuren-remix}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 October 2015 Armin van Buuren released the next single from ''Embrace'' called \"Strong Ones\" featuring Cimo Fr\u00e4nkel. This was followed by the release of his collaboration with [[Cosmic Gate]] \"Embargo\" on 22 October 2015. To accompany the album's release, Van Buuren announced the return of the ''[[Armin Only]]'' series of parties.\n\nThis edition of the tour will be titled ''[[Armin Only]]: Embrace'' and is set to take place throughout both 2015 and 2016. As the title of the tour suggests, it will be based around the collection of music that he's showcased on his new album.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2016/01/first-dates-armin-only-world-tour-may-6th7th-in-the-netherlands/|title = First dates Armin Only world tour: May 6th/7th in the Netherlands|website = Web site of DJ/Producer Armin van Buuren.|access-date = 2016-03-03}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 February 2017, Armin van Buuren officially opened a new A State of Trance radio show studio in Amsterdam as part of his celebrations for the 800th episode of the radio show. The studio is located in the Armada headquarters.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7677720/armin-van-buuren-a-state-of-trance-radio-studio-amsterdam |title=Peak Into Armin Van Buuren's New ASOT Radio Studio, Live Video Streams Start Today: Exclusive |last=Bein |first=Kat |date=2 February 2017 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=9 June 2017}}</ref> With the new accommodations made possible by the studio, he introduced a new segment of the radio show called Service for Dreamers where he invites fans to send in their favorite trance tracks that have a special meaning to them. Every week one track gets chosen to be featured live on the show and introduced by the fans of the radio show live, either by a walk-in, phone call, Skype or other means of contact.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.edmsauce.com/2017/02/07/exclusive-interview-armin-van-buuren-embracing-music/ |title=[Exclusive Interview] Armin van Buuren: Embracing the Music |last=Vargas |first=Ulises |date=7 February 2017 |website=edmsauce |access-date=9 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Armin van Buuren announced he will be releasing an online MasterClass sharing his expertise in electronic music production.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8055125/armin-van-buuren-masterclass-teach-fans-to-dj|title=Armin van Buuren Teaches Fans to DJ With MasterClass: Exclusive|work=Billboard|accessdate=2018-02-22}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 April 2017, Armin van Buuren performed at the Heineken stage in [[Shanghai]], in the first Formula 1 Festival along with [[Angela Chang]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2018/4/shanghai-to-host-heineken-f1-festival.html|title=Shanghai to host Heineken F1 Festival|work=Formula1.com|accessdate=2018-04-05}}</ref>\n\nArmin performed a seven-hour-long set at the Romania Untold Festival on 6 August 2018, clocking from 2:00&nbsp;a.m. to after 9:00&nbsp;a.m.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://dancingastronaut.com/2018/08/armin-van-buuren-throws-seven-hour-trance-set-untold-festival-watch/ |title=Armin van Buuren throws a seven hour trance set at Untold Festival [WATCH] |last=Stack |first=Chris |date=2018-08-06 |website=[[Dancing Astronaut]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807052117/https://dancingastronaut.com/2018/08/armin-van-buuren-throws-seven-hour-trance-set-untold-festival-watch/ |archive-date=2018-08-07 |accessdate=2018-08-07}}</ref> This outlasted his previous 2017 ASOT performance, which had gone on for five hours.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youredm.com/2017/08/06/armin-van-buuren-pulls-nighter-untold-music-festival-5-hour-set-watch/ |title=Armin Van Buuren Pulls All-nighter for Untold Music Festival With 5 Hour Set |last=Powell |first=Karlie |date=2017-08-06 |website=Your EDM |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122214757/https://www.youredm.com/2017/08/06/armin-van-buuren-pulls-nighter-untold-music-festival-5-hour-set-watch/ |archive-date=2018-01-22 |accessdate=2018-08-07}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: ''Balance''===\nOn October 6, 2019 he performed at [[Republic Square, Yerevan]], Armenia as an opening act for the [[World_Information_Technology_and_Services_Alliance#World_Congress_on_IT_(WCIT)|World Congress on Information Technology]] (WCIT).<ref>{{cite web |title=WCIT 2019 grand opening in Yerevan: Armin van Buuren on stage! |url=https://style.news.am/eng/news/63985/wcit-2019-grand-opening-in-yerevan-armin-van-buuren-on-stage!.html |website=style.news.am |date=6 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 October 2019, Armin released his seventh studio album, ''[[Balance (Armin van Buuren album)|Balance]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.edmtunes.com/2019/09/armin-van-buuren-announces-album-title-and-asot-950-event|title=Armin van Buuren announces album title and ASOT 950 Event|first=Scott|last=Lombardo|date=September 5, 2019|website=EDMTunes|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Armin van Buuren discography}}\n* ''[[76 (album)|76]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[Shivers (album)|Shivers]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Imagine (Armin van Buuren album)|Imagine]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Mirage (Armin van Buuren album)|Mirage]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Intense]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[Embrace (Armin van Buuren album)|Embrace]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Balance (Armin van Buuren album)|Balance]]'' (2019)\n\n== Honors ==\nIn 2011, van Buuren was appointed Officer of the [[Order of Orange Nassau]] for his services to music.<ref name=\"officer\"/>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Armin van Buuren}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Armin van Buuren}}\n* {{official website|http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/}}\n* [https://www.armadamusic.com/artists/armin-van-buuren Artist Page on ArmadaMusic.com]\n* {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p335537|label=Armin van Buuren}}\n* {{Discogs artist}}\n* {{MusicBrainz artist|id=477b8c0c-c5fc-4ad2-b5b2-191f0bf2a9df|name=Armin van Buuren}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=2226634|name=Armin van Buuren}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Erol Alkan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=''[[Mixmag]]'' Number 1 DJ|years=2007}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ti\u00ebsto]]}}\n<!-- {{succession box\n | before =\n | title = Beatport Music Awards: Best Trance Artist\n | years = 2008\u20132010\n | after =\n}} -->\n{{s-bef|before=[[Paul van Dyk]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=2|title=''[[DJ Mag]]'' Number 1 DJ|years=2007\u20132010<br>2012}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[David Guetta]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[David Guetta]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Hardwell]]}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{Armin van Buuren}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards for Armin van Buuren\n| list =\n{{DJ Mag Top 100 DJs Poll \u2212 No 1 DJ|state=collapsed}} \n{{DJ Award for Best International DJ |state=collapsed}}\n{{DJ Award for Best Trance DJ |state=collapsed}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buuren, Armin van}} <!-- check authority control-->\n[[Category:Armin van Buuren| ]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ableton Live users]]\n[[Category:Armada Music artists]]\n[[Category:Club DJs]]\n[[Category:Dance-pop musicians]]\n[[Category:Dutch DJs]]\n[[Category:Dutch house musicians]]\n[[Category:Dutch record producers]]\n[[Category:Dutch trance musicians]]\n[[Category:Electro house musicians]]\n[[Category:Eurodance musicians]]\n[[Category:People from Koudekerk aan den Rijn]]\n[[Category:People from Leiden]]\n[[Category:Remixers]]\n[[Category:Trance musicians]]\n[[Category:Dutch radio personalities]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of Orange-Nassau]]\n[[Category:Progressive house musicians]]\n[[Category:Juno Award for Dance Recording of the Year winners]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Van Buuren|other people with this surname|Van Buuren (surname)}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Dutch name|Van Buuren|Buuren}}\n{{distinguish|Armand van Helden}}\n{{short description|Dutch DJ}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}}\n{{infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = Armin van Buuren\n| honorific_suffix = [[Order of Orange-Nassau|OON]]\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image            = Armin van Buuren Armin Only Embrace 2017.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = \n| caption          = Van Buuren performing at the Armin Only Embrace show in Kiev, 2017\n| birth_name       = Armin Jozef Jacobus Dani\u00ebl van Buuren\n| alias            = Rising Star\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1976|12|25}}\n| birth_place      = [[Leiden]], [[Netherlands]]<ref name=\"armadaartistpg\">{{cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/artist/armin-van-buuren/|accessdate= 17 December 2011|title=Armin van Buuren \u2013 Armada Music}}</ref>\n| origin           = [[Koudekerk aan den Rijn]], [[Netherlands]]\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Uplifting trance]]|[[progressive trance]]|[[House music|house]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pro.beatport.com/track/youtopia-feat-adam-young-radio-edit/3144682|title=Armin Van Buuren releases a house single \"Youtopia\" for the Mirage album|publisher=Beatport.com|date=2014-01-20|accessdate=2015-11-07|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117024832/https://pro.beatport.com/track/youtopia-feat-adam-young-radio-edit/3144682|archivedate=17 November 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>|[[progressive house]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pro.beatport.com/track/strong-ones-feat-cimo-frankel-extended-mix/7210464 |title=Armin Van Buuren releases a progressive house single \"Strong Ones\" for the Embrace album|publisher=Beatport.com|date=2014-01-20 |accessdate=2015-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://pro.beatport.com/track/drowning-feat-laura-v-radio-edit/1801569 |title=Armin Van Buuren releases a progressive house single \"Drowning\" for the Mirage album |publisher=Beatport.com |date=2014-01-20 |accessdate=2015-11-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117015615/https://pro.beatport.com/track/drowning-feat-laura-v-radio-edit/1801569 |archivedate=17 November 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>|[[electro house]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pro.beatport.com/track/another-you-feat-mr-probz-extended-mix/7244664 |title=Armin Van Buuren releases a electro house single \"Another You\" for the Embrace album|publisher=Beatport.com|date=2014-01-20 |accessdate=2015-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://pro.beatport.com/track/ping-pong-original-mix/5330637 |title=Armin Van Buuren releases a electro house single \"Ping Pong\" |publisher=Beatport.com|date=2014-01-20 |accessdate=2015-11-07}}</ref>|[[big room house]]|[[dance-pop]]|[[psytrance]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://djmag.com/content/armin-drops-brand-new-psy-trance-track-%E2%80%98blah-blah-blah%E2%80%99-listen |title=Armin Drops Brand New Psy-trance Track, 'Blah Blah Blah': Listen |date=18 May 2018 |website=[[DJ Mag]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180520074315/https://djmag.com/content/armin-drops-brand-new-psy-trance-track-%E2%80%98blah-blah-blah%E2%80%99-listen |archive-date=20 May 2018 |accessdate=21 May 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|DJ|record producer|remixer}}\n| instrument       = {{hlist|[[Synthesizer]]|[[drum machine]]}}\n| years_active     = 1996\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Armada Music|Armada]]|A State of Trance|Armind|[[Kontor Records|Kontor]]|[[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]]|[[Sony Music|SME]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Gaia (band)|Gaia]]|Rising Star|[[Perpetuous Dreamer]]|Alibi}}\n| website          = {{URL|arminvanbuuren.com}}\n{{Infobox person\n| child            = yes\n| signature        = Armin van Buuren autograph.svg\n}}}}\n'''Armin Jozef Jacobus Dani\u00ebl van Buuren''' {{post-nominals|post-noms=[[Order of Orange-Nassau|OON]]}} ({{IPAc-en|v|\u00e6|n|_|\u02c8|b|j|\u028a\u0259r|\u0259|n}} {{respell|van|_|BEWR|\u0259n}},<ref>Van Buuren's own pronunciation that can be heard on ''A State of Trance''.</ref> {{IPA-nl|\u02c8\u0251rm\u026an \u02c8jo\u02d0z\u0259f j\u0251\u02c8ko\u02d0b\u028fs \u02c8da\u02d0ni\u02ccj\u025bl v\u0251n \u02c8by\u02d0r\u0259(n)|lang}}; born 25 December 1976)<ref name=\"armadaartistpg\" /> is a Dutch DJ, record producer and remixer from [[Leiden]]. Since 2001, he has hosted ''[[A State of Trance]]'' (ASOT), a weekly radio show, which is broadcast to nearly 40&nbsp;million listeners in 84 countries on over 100 FM radio stations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/about/|title=About \u2013 A State of Trance|accessdate=19 May 2016}}</ref> According to ''DJs And Festivals'', \"the radio show propelled him to stardom and helped cultivate an interest in trance music around the world.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.djsandfestivals.com/2015/armin-van-buuren-to-make-ims-asia-pacific-debut/|title=Armin van Buuren to make IMS Asia-Pacific debut -|date=2015-12-07|website=www.djsandfestivals.com|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160812043428/http://www.djsandfestivals.com/2015/armin-van-buuren-to-make-ims-asia-pacific-debut/|archivedate=12 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nVan Buuren has won a number of accolades. He has been ranked the number one DJ by ''[[DJ Mag]]'' a record of five times, four years in a row.<ref>{{cite web|title=17 Armada DJ's in DJ Mag Top 100. Though\u2013 Armin is No. 1 again!|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2012/10/17-armada-djs-in-dj-mag-top-100-armin-is-1-again/|accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref> He was ranked fourth on the ''DJ Mag'' Top 100 DJs list in 2015, 2016, and 2019,<ref>{{cite web |title=top 100 DJ's 2019 |url=https://djmag.com/top100djs |website=djmag.com |accessdate=15 November 2019}}</ref> and third in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://djmag.com/top100dj|title=Top 100 DJs {{!}} DJMag.com|website=djmag.com|access-date=2017-06-01}}</ref> In 2014, he was nominated for a [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording]] for his single \"[[This Is What It Feels Like]]\" featuring [[Trevor Guthrie]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5819883/grammy-awards-2014-full-nominations-list-complete-nominees|title=Grammy Awards 2014: Full Nominations List|website=Billboard|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> which makes him the fourth trance artist ever to receive a [[Grammy Award]] nomination.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.djmastercourse.com/famous-progressive-trance-djs/|title=The Most Famous Progressive Trance DJs Of All Time|date=2015-03-02|website=DJ Master Course|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821024001/https://www.djmastercourse.com/famous-progressive-trance-djs/|archivedate=21 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In the United States, he holds the record for most entries, twenty-one, on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Dance/Electronic Albums]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|last=Murray|first=Gordon|title=Armin van Buuren Sets Record on Dance/Electronic Albums Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/code/5869512/armin-van-buuren-sets-record-on-dance-electronic-albums-chart|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=24 May 2014|date=10 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nArmin van Buuren was born in [[Leiden]], on 25 December 1976,<ref name=\"armadaartistpg\" /> but grew up in [[Koudekerk aan den Rijn]]. Van Buuren started making music when he was 14.<ref name=\"Interview with Armin van Buuren\">{{cite web|url=http://dancemusic.about.com/cs/interviews/a/IntAVBuuren.htm|title=Interview with Armin van Buuren|publisher=About.com|accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref> He was inspired by French electronic music composer [[Jean-Michel Jarre]].<ref name=\"Interview with Armin van Buuren\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.synthtopia.com/content/2009/05/29/armin-van-buuren-fanboy/|title=Armin van Buuren, Fanboy|last=|first=|date=|website=synthopia|publisher=|access-date=|accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref> Van Buuren graduated from the [[Stedelijk Gymnasium Leiden]] in 1995, and studied law at [[Leiden University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nextshark.com/armin-van-buuren-interview/|title=How a Simple Law Student Became an EDM Legend|date=2015-06-16|website=NextShark|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> He began working as a DJ in Club Nexus, playing multiple sets a week, most of which lasted six or more hours.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.beatport.com/en/focus-on-the-netherlands-armin-van-buuren/|title=Focus on the Netherlands: Armin Van Buuren|date=2010-10-08|website=Beatport News (EN)|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 1999, he met Dave Lewis who introduced him as a DJ in England and the United States.<ref name=\":1\" /> As his musical career began to take off, he put his law degree on hold, but he did return to graduate from law school in 2003.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://legacy.lawstreetmedia.com/schools/9-celebrities-didnt-know-law-degrees/|title=7 Celebrities You Didn't Know Had Law Degrees - Law Street (TM)|date=2015-07-15|website=Law Street (TM)|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2009, Van Buuren married Erika van Thiel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.exqlusiv.com/8-pictures-of-djs-with-their-girlfriend-wife-part-2/|title=8 pictures of DJ's with their girlfriend / wife [Part 2]|date=2015-08-08|website=exQlusiv.com|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> Their daughter Fenna was born in July 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/music/armin-van-buuren-puts-mansion-miami-into-a-state-of-trance-on-june-2-6441028|title=Armin van Buuren Puts Mansion Miami Into A State of Trance on June 2|last=Gonzalez|first=Victor|date=2012-05-21|website=Miami New Times|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> Van Buuren announced just hours before he was due to headline the main stage at [[Tomorrowland (festival)|Tomorrowland]] (27 July 2013) that his wife had given birth to a son, Remy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/list/5166011/top-6-tomorrowland-moments-you-can-watch-right-now|title=Top 6 Tomorrowland Moments You Can Watch Right Now|website=Billboard|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 February 2018, Van Buuren explored his family history in an episode of the TV series ''Verborgen verleden'', the Dutch version of the UK series ''[[Who Do You Think You Are? (UK TV series)|Who Do You Think You Are?]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ntr.nl/Verborgen-Verleden/77/detail/Armin-van-Buuren/VPWON_1280993 |title=Armin van Buuren |language=Dutch |website=[[Omroep NTR|NTR]] |accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===1996\u20131999: Early career and success===\nIn 1996, Van Buuren released ''EP'' and ''Push'' on Timeless Records. Van Buuren had his first success with a track called \"Blue Fear\", which was released under the Cyber Records label in 1997. Another successful track, \"Communication\", was released under the same label and became popular in [[Ibiza]], Spain in the summer of 1999.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.magneticmag.com/2015/05/armin-van-buuren-bio/|title=Armin van Buuren Bio|last=Editorial|first=Magnetic|date=5 May 2015|website=Magnetic Magazine|publisher=|access-date=21 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160713061945/http://www.magneticmag.com/2015/05/armin-van-buuren-bio/|archive-date=13 July 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> After being signed to [[AM PM Records]],<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/store/music/artist/armin-van-buuren/47780200-0200-11db-89ca-0019b92a3933/bio?display=grid|title=Armin Van Buuren Bio|last=|first=|date=|website=microsoft.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> this track entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] at No.&nbsp;18 in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/3672/armin/?Day=&Month=&Year=1963|title=ARMIN {{!}} full Official Chart History {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\n\nIn the beginning of 1999, Van Buuren started his label Armind together with United Recordings. The first release, Gig \u2013 \"One\", was well received. The second release, \"Touch Me\" under the name Rising Star, was signed to [[Ministry of Sound]] in the UK, before the record was released. By the time of his third release, Gimmick \u2013 \"Free\" was signed to [[R&S Records]]. During this year, he remixed the first two singles of [[Gouryella]] (''Gouryella'' and ''Walhalla'') and, under the guise of Rising Star, produced a remix of ''L'Esperanza'', a song by [[Airscape]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ferrycorsten.com/news/ferry-corsten-announces-gouryella-live|title=From the studio to the stage: Ferry Corsten announces Gouryella live!|publisher=[[Flashover Recordings]]|date=2 December 2015|accessdate=8 February 2017|author=Flashover Recordings|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912040028/http://ferrycorsten.com/news/ferry-corsten-announces-gouryella-live|archive-date=12 September 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/music/airscape-lesperanza-armin-van-buurens-rising-star-mix/ |title=Airscape - L'Esperanza (Armin Van Buuren's Rising Star Mix) |authorlink=Armada Music |website=[[Armada Music]] |access-date=8 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n===2000\u20132004: ''76'' and ''A State of Trance'' series===\nIn 2000, Van Buuren started his own Armin van Buuren compilation series, a mix of [[progressive house]] and [[vocal trance]] styles of music.<!-- according to who? --> His first compilation album, ''A State of Trance'' (not to be confused with his weekly ''[[A State of Trance]]'' radio shows), sold 10,000 copies<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gazettereview.com/2016/04/richest-djs-world/|title=The Top 10 Richest DJs in the World - The Gazette Review|last=Deml|first=Jessica|date=2016-04-09|website=The Gazette Review|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> and contains Van Buuren's remix of [[Moogwai]], \"Viola\". Teaming up with [[Ti\u00ebsto]], two new projects were born: Major League \u2013 \"Wonder Where You Are?\" was released on [[Black Hole Recordings]] and Alibi \u2013 \"Eternity\" was released on Armind. \"Eternity\" received club and chart success and was signed to [[Paul van Dyk]]'s imprint [[Vandit Records]]. Another major collaboration followed this. Together with [[Ferry Corsten]], Van Buuren recorded a [[riff]] titled \"Exhale<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2006/11/907/|title=Armin van Buuren - 10 Years - Order now! - Armada Music|date=2006-11-06|website=Armada Music|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\" for the System F album, ''[[Out of the Blue (Ferry Corsten album)|Out of the Blue]]''. Released as a single, this track reached Gold status.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ultramusic.com/artist/ferry-corsten/|title=Ferry Corsten / Ultra Music / Ultra Records / Ultra|website=Ultra Music / Ultra Records / Ultra|access-date=2016-06-21|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160503043754/http://ultramusic.com/artist/ferry-corsten/|archivedate=3 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Under the pseudonym [[Gaia (Armin van Buuren alias)|Gaia]] he released \"4 Elements\" on Captivating Sounds, a sub-label of [[Warner Brothers]].<ref>http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/music/gaia-4-elements/</ref>\n\nHis second album, ''Basic Instinct'' featured a new track: \"Perpetuous Dreamer\" \u2013 \"The Sound of Goodbye\". This track entered the Dutch charts in June 2001 at number 26. Later in the year, the track hit No.&nbsp;1 on the [[Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Music/Club Play]] chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ellesdegraaf.net/elles_bio.html|title=Elles de Graaf {{!}} Biography|last=Krogull|first=Andreas|website=www.ellesdegraaf.net|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> The third album, ''In Motion'' was released 6 August 2001. A fourth album, ''Transparence'', followed in 2002. In 2003, he worked with such artists such as DJ Seth Alan Fannin throughout a global tour on Dance Revolution in Europe, selling out to crowds of 20,000 people in the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://themusicessentials.com/artist-of-the-month-february-2015-armin-van-buuren/|title=King Of Trance: Our Artist Of The Month For February 2015, Armin van Buuren! {{!}} T.H.E - Music Essentials|date=2015-02-02|website=T.H.E - Music Essentials|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820150227/http://themusicessentials.com/artist-of-the-month-february-2015-armin-van-buuren|archive-date=20 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2001, Van Buuren started his own radio show on [[ID&T]] Radio<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2006/05/803/|title=A State of Trance celebrates its 250th broadcast! - Armada Music|date=2006-05-10|website=Armada Music|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> (traditionally broadcast in Dutch and later English since ASOT 183). In this weekly two-hour show, entitled ''[[A State of Trance]]'', he plays the latest popular trance music tracks, and publishes the artists and track titles on his website. When ID&T Radio changed genres in 2004, Van Buuren moved ''A State of Trance'' to [[Fresh FM (Netherlands)|Fresh FM]] and later [[SLAM!FM]], two Dutch radio stations. It is now a weekly feature on [[Radio 538]], the Dutch radio station,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.538.nl/programma/37/a-state-of-trance|title=A State Of Trance|website=538.nl|language=nl-NL|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> [[DI.FM]], an online radio station,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.di.fm/shows/a-state-of-trance|title=A State Of Trance with Armin van Buuren|website=Digitally Imported|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> and on [[XM Satellite Radio]], [[Electric Area|channel 52]] in the United States and Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.siriusxm.com/electricarea/weeklyschedule|title=Weekly Schedule - Electric Area|website=SiriusXM|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> A complete list of stations that broadcast ''A State of Trance'' can be found at the ASOT section of Armin's website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/stations/|title=Radio stations broadcasting A State of Trance|website=A State of Trance|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, he had a residency at Glow in Washington D.C.,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.clubglow.com/djs/armin-in-dc-a-14-year-old-journey/|title=Armin van Buuren + Glow Washington DC \u2013 A 14 Year Old Journey|website=Club Glow Washington DC|access-date=2016-06-21}}</ref> and played across North America. He regularly appeared at [[Amnesia (nightclub)|Amnesia]] on the island of [[Ibiza]], Balearic Islands, Spain. In October that year, Van Buuren was voted number 5 in the ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''.\n\nIn June 2003, Van Buuren celebrated the 100th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Bloomingdale, [[Bloemendaal aan Zee]], Netherlands and released his debut studio album, ''[[76 (album)|76]]'', a 76-minute album divided into 13 tracks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/discography/?release=Arma056|title=Armin van Buuren \u2013 76 \u2013 Release|accessdate=10 January 2012}}</ref> In the same year he was voted No. 3 in the ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]'' and held third place for the next two years (2004, 2005). Also in 2004, Van Buuren remixed the ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]'' theme song into a trance hit.\n\n===2005\u20132006: ''Shivers''===\n[[File:Armin van Buuren 2005 (cropped).jpg|thumb|240px|Armin van Buuren at [[Sensation (event)|Sensation White]] 2005]]\n\nOn 2 June 2005, he celebrated the 200th episode of ''[[A State of Trance]]'' at the [[Museumplein]] of [[Amsterdam]]. On 8 August 2005, Van Buuren released his second studio album, ''[[Shivers (album)|Shivers]]''. On the album Van Buuren worked with artists such as Pakistani-American singer [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]], English singer [[Justine Suissa]] and American trance duo [[Gabriel & Dresden]]. On 25 May 2006, he celebrated with various artists the 250th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Asta, [[The Hague]], Netherlands. He was voted number two in the 2006 ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''. On 17 May 2007, he celebrated with various artists the 300th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Pettelaarse Schans, [['s-Hertogenbosch]], Netherlands.\n\n===2007\u20132009: ''Imagine''===\nVan Buuren was elected best DJ in the world in the 2007 ''[[DJ Mag]]'' edition. On 12 January 2008, Van Buuren was given the \"Buma Cultuur Pop Award,\" the most prestigious Dutch music award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.armadamusic.com/news/pop-award-goes-to-armin-van-buuren|title=Pop Award goes to Armin van Buuren|last=|first=|date=|website=Armada Music|publisher=|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-06}}</ref> On 17 April 2008, Van Buuren released his third studio album, ''[[Imagine (Armin van Buuren album)|Imagine]]''. It features collaboration with singers such as [[Jacqueline Govaert]] of [[Krezip]]. The album debuted at number one on the [[MegaCharts|Dutch Albums Chart]]. The second single released from the album, [[In and Out of Love (Armin van Buuren song)|\"In and Out of Love\"]], featuring [[Sharon den Adel]] from the band [[Within Temptation]], has spawned a music video that has been viewed over 212 million times on YouTube.<ref name=\"YouTube\">{{cite web|author=Armada Music|author-link=Armada Music|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TxvpctgU_s8|title=Armin van Buuren ft. Sharon den Adel \u2013 In and Out of Love (Official Music Video)|publisher=YouTube|date=6 August 2008|accessdate=14 July 2012}}</ref> Since the release of ''Imagine'', Van Buuren has been working with [[Benno de Goeij]] of [[Rank 1]] on solo productions and remixes.{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}} On 1 May 2008, he celebrated with various artists the 350th episode of ''A State of Trance'' at Noxx, [[Antwerp]], Belgium. He was voted No. 1 in the 2008 ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]'' again.\n\nHe collaborated with his brother, guitarist Eller van Buuren, at [[Together as One (festival)|Together As One]] in Los Angeles, U.S., on New Year's Eve 2009, as well as on Armin's 2008 studio album ''[[Imagine (Armin van Buuren album)|Imagine]]''. His performance with his brother at Together As One was also the last event of his ''Armin Only: Imagine'' world tour. To celebrate the 400th episode of ''A State of Trance'', he performed at three shows with various artists in April, 2009 at Club Butan, [[Wuppertal]], Germany, [[AIR (nightclub)|AIR]], Birmingham, United Kingdom and Maassilo, [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]].\n\nAlso in 2009, Foreign Media Games announced the production of ''[[Armin van Buuren: In the Mix]]'', a [[music video game]] being produced in collaboration with Cloud 9 Music and Van Buuren's Armada Music label. The title was released on 12 November 2010 exclusively for the [[Wii|Wii console]].<ref>[http://worthplaying.com/article/2009/10/30/news/69826/ 'In The Mix: Featuring Armin van Buuren' (Wii) Shows Off Career Mode \u2013 Screen], 30 October 2009.</ref> He was voted number one DJ in the 2009 ''[[DJ Mag]]'' for the third consecutive year.\n\n===2010\u20132012: ''Mirage'' and appointment to the Order of Orange-Nassau===\nOn 3 March 2010, Van Buuren was awarded with the [[Golden Harp]] for his musical work and contribution to Dutch music, by [[Buma/Stemra]] at the 2010 Buma Harpen Gala in [[Hilversum]], Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bumacultuur.nl/nl/nieuws/171/buma-gouden-en-zilveren-harpen-buma-exportprijs-en-beste-nederlandse-lied-uitgereikt|title=Buma Gouden \u2013 en Zilveren Harpen, Buma Exportprijs en Beste Nederlandse Lied uitgereikt|date=3 March 2010|publisher=[[BUMA/STEMRA|Buma Cultuur]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=25 March 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100420102925/http://www.bumacultuur.nl/nl/nieuws/171/buma-gouden-en-zilveren-harpen-buma-exportprijs-en-beste-nederlandse-lied-uitgereikt|archivedate=20 April 2010|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2010/03/armin-van-buuren-awarded-with-gouden-harp/|title=Armin van Buuren awarded with Gouden Harp|date=4 March 2010|publisher=[[Armada Music]]|accessdate=25 March 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100408055756/http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2010/03/armin-van-buuren-awarded-with-gouden-harp/| archivedate= 8 April 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> To celebrate the 450th episode of ''A State of Trance'', he performed with various artists at five shows across two continents. The locations were: [[The Guvernment]], Toronto, Canada on 1 April 2010, [[Roseland Ballroom]], New York City on 2 April and on 3 April again, Expo Arena, [[Bratislava]], Slovakia on 9 April and [[Centennial Hall]], [[Wroclaw]], Poland on 24 April.\n\nOn 23 June 2010, it was announced that Van Buuren's fourth studio album, ''[[Mirage (Armin van Buuren album)|Mirage]]'' was due to be released on 10 September.<ref>{{cite web|title=New single Full Focus available tonight at 00:00 |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/362/ |publisher=arminvanbuuren.com |date=23 June 2010 |accessdate=23 June 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100626060738/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/362/ |archivedate=26 June 2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> The first single \"Full Focus\", was released through [[iTunes Store]] on 24 June.<ref>{{cite web|title=New single Full Focus out now! \" Armin van Buuren|url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/06/new-single-full-focus-out-now/|publisher=arminvanbuuren.com|accessdate=10 July 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203195326/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/06/new-single-full-focus-out-now/|archivedate=3 December 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The song peaked at number 60 in the Netherlands. One of the confirmed tracks from the album is a collaboration with English singer [[Sophie Ellis-Bextor]] called \"[[Not Giving Up on Love]]\", which was released as a single from Bextor's fourth studio album, ''[[Make a Scene]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Nick|title=Music \u2013 News \u2013 Ellis-Bextor switches single plans|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a223927/ellis-bextor-switches-single-plans.html|date=7 June 2010|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=10 July 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100610213419/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a223927/ellis-bextor-switches-single-plans.html| archivedate= 10 June 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Nick|title=Armin werkte 'harder dan ooit' aan nieuwe plaat|url=http://www.depers.nl/entertainment/489763/Armin-werkte-harder-dan-ooit.html|language=Dutch|date=24 June 2010|publisher=DePers.nl|accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> Armin also wrote a song for English singer [[Seal (musician)|Seal]], but due to the release of his greatest hits album, ''[[Hits (Seal album)|Hits]]'', the collaboration never came together.<ref>{{cite web|last=van Luling|first=Dennis|title=Armin van Buuren verovert ook Zuid-Amerika|url=http://www.nu.nl/muziek/2281427/armin-van-buuren-verovert-zuid-amerika.html|language=Dutch|date=30 June 2010|publisher=[[NU.nl]]|accessdate=10 July 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100703135813/http://www.nu.nl/muziek/2281427/armin-van-buuren-verovert-zuid-amerika.html| archivedate= 3 July 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> On 12 September 2010, Van Buuren launched \"A State of Sundays\", a new weekly 24-hour radio show aired on Sirius XM Radio.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/09/armin-launches-a-state-of-sundays-on-sirius-xm/ |title=Armin launches A State of Sundays on Sirius XM \" Armin van Buuren |publisher=Arminvanbuuren.com |accessdate=2012-08-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120817032235/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/09/armin-launches-a-state-of-sundays-on-sirius-xm/ |archivedate=17 August 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> On 20 October 2010, Van Buuren won the award for Most Popular International DJ presented by The Golden Gnomes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldengnomeawards.com/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100917193926/http://www.goldengnomeawards.com/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2010-09-17 |title=Golden Gnome Awards |publisher=Golden Gnome Awards |accessdate=2012-08-30 }}</ref> A week later he was announced, for the fourth year running, as the number one DJ in ''[[DJ Mag]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/10/armin-van-buuren-no-1-dj-in-the-dj-mag-top-100-again/ |title=Armin van Buuren no 1 DJ in the DJ Mag Top 100 again! \" Armin van Buuren |publisher=Arminvanbuuren.com |accessdate=2012-08-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030015708/http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2010/10/armin-van-buuren-no-1-dj-in-the-dj-mag-top-100-again/ |archivedate=30 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe 2010 edition of ''[[Armin Only]]: Mirage'' kicked off in November 2010, in [[Utrecht, Netherlands]], and was followed by shows in [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Kiev]], Buenos Aires, [[Melbourne]], [[Beirut]], [[Pozna\u0144]], Moscow and [[Bratislava]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminonly.com/shows-tickets/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100627145226/http://www.arminonly.com/shows-tickets/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2010-06-27 |title=Shows & Tickets \" Armin Only |publisher=Arminonly.com |accessdate=2012-08-30 }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Armin on air.jpg|thumb|240px|right|Van Buuren broadcasting the milestone 500th episode of his ''[[A State of Trance]]'' show at the official pre-party, live from Club Trinity in [[Cape Town]] on 17 March 2011.]]\nIn March and April, 2011, celebrating the 500th episode of his radio show, Van Buuren performed five live shows along with various artists; the first was in [[Johannesburg]], South Africa at MTN Expo Centre, and the second in [[Miami]]'s [[Ultra Music Festival]]. He then performed in [[Argentina]] at [[Estadio G.E.B.A.|GEBA]] in Buenos Aires, followed by a large event at Brabanthallen in [[Den Bosch]], Netherlands which included more than 30 DJs from countries all over the world and was attended by over 30,000 people. The final show was held in Sydney on 16 April at [[Acer Arena]]. In 2011, Van Buuren was appointed Officer of the [[Order of Oranje-Nassau]] for services to Dutch dance and music economy.<ref name=\"officer\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.armadamusic.com/news/armin-named-officer-in-the-order-of-oranje-nassau |title=Armin named Officer in the Order of Oranje-Nassau! |authorlink=Armada Music |website=Armada Music |publication-date=30 April 2011 |access-date=10 August 2017}}</ref> That year he also received the [[Key to the City|Key]] to ([[Freedom of the City|Freedom]]) of [[Leiden]] from the City Mayor, as well as being voted No. 2 in the 2011 ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''.\n\nTo celebrate the 550th episode of ''A State of Trance'', he performed with various artists on two different continents during fourth weeks. The show was called ''A State of Trance 550: Invasion''. The first event was celebrated at [[Ministry of Sound]] in London on 1 March 2012. On 7 March, Moscow held the second event at [[Expocentre]]. [[Kiev]]'s show was performed at International Exhibition Centre on 10 March. On 17 March, as part of the [[Beyond Wonderland]] festival in Los Angeles and on 25 March at the [[Ultra Music Festival]] in Miami. On 31 March, the biggest and final edition of ASOT 550 took place in the Brabanthallen of [[Den Bosch]], Netherlands. On 19 October 2012, Van Buuren was announced for a fifth non-consecutive year as the world's number one DJ according to ''[[DJ Magazine|DJ Mag]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2012/10/armin-van-buuren-back-to-number-one-in-dj-mag-top-100/ |title=Armin van Buuren back to number no one in DJ Mag Top 100! \" Armin van Buuren |publisher=Arminvanbuuren.com |date= |accessdate=20 October 2012}}</ref>\n\nTo celebrate the 600th episode of ''A State of Trance'', Van Buuren announced that he would perform with various artists all around the world in early 2014. The show was called ''A State of Trance 600: The Expedition''. It was announced that the show would tour the world, including stops in [[Madrid]], [[Mexico City]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Minsk]], [[Sofia]], [[Beirut]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Mumbai]], [[Miami]], [[Guatemala City]], [[New York City]], and [[Den Bosch]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/a-state-of-trance-600 |title=A State of Trance 600 \" A State of Trance |publisher=Astateoftrance.com |date= |accessdate=2013-07-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ASOT 650 New Horizons 2014 dates announced, tour will be 'massive,' says Armin van Buuren|url=http://www.dancingastronaut.com/2013/10/asot-650-new-horizons-2014-dates-announced-tour-will-be-massive-says-armin-van-buuren/}}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''Intense''===\nThe first single of Van Buuren's fifth studio album, ''[[Intense]]'', titled \"[[This Is What It Feels Like]]\", featured Canadian singer and songwriter [[Trevor Guthrie]], and was released on 5 April 2013. The single nominated for a [[Grammy Award]] for Best Dance Recording.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newson6.com/story/21641513/1-dj-armin-van-buuren-releases-1st-single-this-is-what-it-feels-like-from-his-5th-artist-album-intense-anaarmada-north-america-april-5th |title=#1 DJ Armin van Buuren Releases 1st Single \"This Is What It Feels Like\" from His 5th Artist Album 'INTENSE' (ANA/ARMADA NORTH AMERICA) April 5th \u2013 NewsOn6.com \u2013 Tulsa, OK |publisher=NewsOn6.com |accessdate=2013-07-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411130254/http://www.newson6.com/story/21641513/1-dj-armin-van-buuren-releases-1st-single-this-is-what-it-feels-like-from-his-5th-artist-album-intense-anaarmada-north-america-april-5th |archivedate=11 April 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The tour for the album, ''[[Armin Only]]: Intense'', was announced on 17 October 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arminonly.com/news-item-details-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101201334/http://www.arminonly.com/news-item-details-19 |url-status=dead |archive-date=1 November 2013 |title=20 Dates and 19 Destinations for Armin Only Intense |publisher=Armin van Buuren |date=17 October 2013 |accessdate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>\n\n30 April 2013 saw the abdication of Queen [[Beatrix of the Netherlands]] in favor of her son, King [[Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands]], who was crowned that day. Van Buuren was the headline act in a performance to a live audience celebrating the King's crowning in Amsterdam. While he was performing live together with the [[Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra]], King [[Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands|Willem-Alexander]], Queen [[Queen M\u00e1xima of the Netherlands|M\u00e1xima]] and their three daughters made an unplanned visit on stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GeVvRGkXTLc |title=Armin van Buuren & The Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra perform for new Dutch king Willem-Alexander |publisher=Armada Music |date=19 May 2013 |accessdate=2013-12-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.demorgen.be/dm/nl/15698/Willem-Alexander/article/detail/1624976/2013/05/01/Uitstapje-koningspaar-stond-niet-in-draaiboeken.dhtml |title='Uitstapje' koningspaar stond niet in draaiboeken ('pleasure-trip' of royal couple was not part of plan of action) |publisher=De Morgen |date=1 May 2013 |accessdate=2013-12-30}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 October 2013, Armin van Buuren was ranked number two DJ in the world by ''[[DJ Mag]]''. On 26 January 2014, Armin van Buuren attended the [[56th Annual Grammy Awards|56th Grammy Awards]], in relation to his Grammy Award nomination for the single featuring Trevor Guthrie, \"This Is What It Feels Like\" in the category of [[Grammy Award for Best Dance Recording|Best Dance Recording]].\n\n===2015\u20132018: ''Embrace''===\n[[File:Armin van Buuren logo.svg|thumb|240px|Van Buuren's DJ logo, used in shows as of 2015]]\nOn 8 May 2015, Armin van Buuren released the first single from his sixth studio album, ''[[Embrace (Armin van Buuren album)|Embrace]]'', which was released on 29 October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astateoftrance.com/news/armin-van-buuren-announces-new-artist-album-embrace/|title=Armin van Buuren announces new artist album|publisher=}}</ref> The single is titled \"[[Another You (Armin van Buuren song)|Another You]]\" featuring [[Mr Probz]]. Three weeks after releasing \"Another You\", Van Buuren also debuted another remix from ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' official theme which is originally made by composer [[Ramin Djawadi]].<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Matt|last=Medved|date=8 June 2015|title='Game of Thrones' Theme Receives Trance Remix By Armin van Buuren|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/6590616/game-of-thrones-theme-armin-van-buuren-remix}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 October 2015 Armin van Buuren released the next single from ''Embrace'' called \"Strong Ones\" featuring Cimo Fr\u00e4nkel. This was followed by the release of his collaboration with [[Cosmic Gate]] \"Embargo\" on 22 October 2015. To accompany the album's release, Van Buuren announced the return of the ''[[Armin Only]]'' series of parties.\n\nThis edition of the tour will be titled ''[[Armin Only]]: Embrace'' and is set to take place throughout both 2015 and 2016. As the title of the tour suggests, it will be based around the collection of music that he's showcased on his new album.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/news/2016/01/first-dates-armin-only-world-tour-may-6th7th-in-the-netherlands/|title = First dates Armin Only world tour: May 6th/7th in the Netherlands|website = Web site of DJ/Producer Armin van Buuren.|access-date = 2016-03-03}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 February 2017, Armin van Buuren officially opened a new A State of Trance radio show studio in Amsterdam as part of his celebrations for the 800th episode of the radio show. The studio is located in the Armada headquarters.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7677720/armin-van-buuren-a-state-of-trance-radio-studio-amsterdam |title=Peak Into Armin Van Buuren's New ASOT Radio Studio, Live Video Streams Start Today: Exclusive |last=Bein |first=Kat |date=2 February 2017 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=9 June 2017}}</ref> With the new accommodations made possible by the studio, he introduced a new segment of the radio show called Service for Dreamers where he invites fans to send in their favorite trance tracks that have a special meaning to them. Every week one track gets chosen to be featured live on the show and introduced by the fans of the radio show live, either by a walk-in, phone call, Skype or other means of contact.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.edmsauce.com/2017/02/07/exclusive-interview-armin-van-buuren-embracing-music/ |title=[Exclusive Interview] Armin van Buuren: Embracing the Music |last=Vargas |first=Ulises |date=7 February 2017 |website=edmsauce |access-date=9 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Armin van Buuren announced he will be releasing an online MasterClass sharing his expertise in electronic music production.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8055125/armin-van-buuren-masterclass-teach-fans-to-dj|title=Armin van Buuren Teaches Fans to DJ With MasterClass: Exclusive|work=Billboard|accessdate=2018-02-22}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 April 2017, Armin van Buuren performed at the Heineken stage in [[Shanghai]], in the first Formula 1 Festival along with [[Angela Chang]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/headlines/2018/4/shanghai-to-host-heineken-f1-festival.html|title=Shanghai to host Heineken F1 Festival|work=Formula1.com|accessdate=2018-04-05}}</ref>\n\nArmin performed a seven-hour-long set at the Romania Untold Festival on 6 August 2018, clocking from 2:00&nbsp;a.m. to after 9:00&nbsp;a.m.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://dancingastronaut.com/2018/08/armin-van-buuren-throws-seven-hour-trance-set-untold-festival-watch/ |title=Armin van Buuren throws a seven hour trance set at Untold Festival [WATCH] |last=Stack |first=Chris |date=2018-08-06 |website=[[Dancing Astronaut]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807052117/https://dancingastronaut.com/2018/08/armin-van-buuren-throws-seven-hour-trance-set-untold-festival-watch/ |archive-date=2018-08-07 |accessdate=2018-08-07}}</ref> This outlasted his previous 2017 ASOT performance, which had gone on for five hours.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youredm.com/2017/08/06/armin-van-buuren-pulls-nighter-untold-music-festival-5-hour-set-watch/ |title=Armin Van Buuren Pulls All-nighter for Untold Music Festival With 5 Hour Set |last=Powell |first=Karlie |date=2017-08-06 |website=Your EDM |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122214757/https://www.youredm.com/2017/08/06/armin-van-buuren-pulls-nighter-untold-music-festival-5-hour-set-watch/ |archive-date=2018-01-22 |accessdate=2018-08-07}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: ''Balance''===\nOn October 6, 2019 he performed at [[Republic Square, Yerevan]], Armenia as an opening act for the [[World_Information_Technology_and_Services_Alliance#World_Congress_on_IT_(WCIT)|World Congress on Information Technology]] (WCIT).<ref>{{cite web |title=WCIT 2019 grand opening in Yerevan: Armin van Buuren on stage! |url=https://style.news.am/eng/news/63985/wcit-2019-grand-opening-in-yerevan-armin-van-buuren-on-stage!.html |website=style.news.am |date=6 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 October 2019, Armin released his seventh studio album, ''[[Balance (Armin van Buuren album)|Balance]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.edmtunes.com/2019/09/armin-van-buuren-announces-album-title-and-asot-950-event|title=Armin van Buuren announces album title and ASOT 950 Event|first=Scott|last=Lombardo|date=September 5, 2019|website=EDMTunes|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Armin van Buuren discography}}\n* ''[[76 (album)|76]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[Shivers (album)|Shivers]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Imagine (Armin van Buuren album)|Imagine]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Mirage (Armin van Buuren album)|Mirage]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Intense]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[Embrace (Armin van Buuren album)|Embrace]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Balance (Armin van Buuren album)|Balance]]'' (2019)\n\n== Honors ==\nIn 2011, van Buuren was appointed Officer of the [[Order of Orange Nassau]] for his services to music.<ref name=\"officer\"/>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Armin van Buuren}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Armin van Buuren}}\n* {{official website|http://www.arminvanbuuren.com/}}\n* [https://www.armadamusic.com/artists/armin-van-buuren Artist Page on ArmadaMusic.com]\n* {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p335537|label=Armin van Buuren}}\n* {{Discogs artist}}\n* {{MusicBrainz artist|id=477b8c0c-c5fc-4ad2-b5b2-191f0bf2a9df|name=Armin van Buuren}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=2226634|name=Armin van Buuren}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Erol Alkan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=''[[Mixmag]]'' Number 1 DJ|years=2007}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ti\u00ebsto]]}}\n<!-- {{succession box\n | before =\n | title = Beatport Music Awards: Best Trance Artist\n | years = 2008\u20132010\n | after =\n}} -->\n{{s-bef|before=[[Paul van Dyk]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=2|title=''[[DJ Mag]]'' Number 1 DJ|years=2007\u20132010<br>2012}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[David Guetta]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[David Guetta]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Hardwell]]}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{Armin van Buuren}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards for Armin van Buuren\n| list =\n{{DJ Mag Top 100 DJ's Poll \u2212 No 1 DJ|state=collapsed}} \n{{DJ Award for Best International DJ |state=collapsed}}\n{{DJ Award for Best Trance DJ |state=collapsed}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buuren, Armin van}} <!-- check authority control-->\n[[Category:Armin van Buuren| ]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ableton Live users]]\n[[Category:Armada Music artists]]\n[[Category:Club DJs]]\n[[Category:Dance-pop musicians]]\n[[Category:Dutch DJs]]\n[[Category:Dutch house musicians]]\n[[Category:Dutch record producers]]\n[[Category:Dutch trance musicians]]\n[[Category:Electro house musicians]]\n[[Category:Eurodance musicians]]\n[[Category:People from Koudekerk aan den Rijn]]\n[[Category:People from Leiden]]\n[[Category:Remixers]]\n[[Category:Trance musicians]]\n[[Category:Dutch radio personalities]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of Orange-Nassau]]\n[[Category:Progressive house musicians]]\n[[Category:Juno Award for Dance Recording of the Year winners]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n", "name_user": "Alistair1978", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armin_van_Buuren"}
{"title_page": "Templemore apparitions", "text_new": "In August and September 1920 the town of [[Templemore]] in [[County Tipperary]], [[Ireland]] was the sight of alleged [[Marian apparition]]s. Thousands of people came to the town daily to see the apparitions.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\">{{cite journal |last1=Reynolds |first1=John |title=The Templemore miracles |journal=History Ireland |date=Jan/Feb 2009 |volume=17 |issue=1 |url=https://www.historyireland.com/20th-century-contemporary-history/the-templemore-miracles/ |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> The affair occurred during the [[Irish War of Independence]] and resulted in a short-lived local truce between the [[Irish Republican Army (1919-1922)|IRA]] and [[Crown forces]].<ref name=\"46MenDead\">{{cite book |last1=Reynolds |first1=John |title=46 Men Dead: The Royal Irish Constabulary in County Tipperary, 1919-22 |date=2016 |publisher=Gill & Macmillan Ltd |page=No page number given |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=OQiWDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> When the truce ended, [[pilgrim]]s stopped coming to the town and the sightings ended. The affair is sometimes referred to as the '''Templemore miracles'''.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Miracles1\">{{cite book |last1=Reynolds |first1=John |title=The Templemore Miracles: Jimmy Walsh, Ceasefires and Moving Statues |date=2019 |publisher=The History Press}}</ref>\n\n==Apparitions==\nIn January 1919 the [[Irish War of Independence]] began. It would last until July 1921. On the night of 16 August 1920, [[British army|British soldiers]] of the [[Northamptonshire Regiment]] attacked Templemore in reprisal for the killing of an [[Royal Irish Constabulary|RIC]] officer by IRA volunteers earlier that day.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> They fired volleys and burned homes and businesses.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> No civilians or IRA men were killed but two soldiers died by accident in the fires.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/>\n\n[[File:Templemore Main Street and Town Hall, 2015.JPG|right|thumb|200px|Main Street including Town Hall in 2015]]Shortly after the attack, a sixteen-year old farm labourer named James Walsh claimed that he was visited by the [[Virgin Mary]] in his cottage in the nearby [[townland]] of Curraheen.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/><ref name=\"LittleBook\">{{cite book|last1=Blake |first1=Debbie |title=The Little Book of Tipperary |date=2018 |publisher=The History Press |page=No page given |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=K51ODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> She told him that she was troubled by what was happening in Ireland.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> At her request he dug a hole in the ground in his bedroom and this soon [[holy well|filled with spring water]].<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> Afterwards he claimed that all three statues of the Virgin Mary in his home [[weeping statue|began to bleed]].<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> He took these statues to Templemore, where the bleeding was witnessed.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> One man who had been crippled for most of his life claimed he was dancing in the streets after seeing the staues. He was the first of many who claimed to have been cured of their ailments in the presence of Walsh or the statues.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/><ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Wilson1\">{{cite book |last1=Wilson |first1=Ann |title=Kitsch, Enchantment and Power: The Bleeding Statues of Templemore. IN: Love Objects: Emotion, Design and Material Culture. |date=2014 |publisher=Bloomsbury Academic |page=94 |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=noXhAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nLocals believed that divine intervention had prevented any of them being killed or wounded during the attack by the British.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> Walsh gathered people around the statues to say the [[rosary]] in [[Irish language|Irish]].<ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> According to Ann Wilson, the statues were seen \u2018as asserting the [[Irish Catholics|Catholic Irish]] identity of the population in the face of the non-Catholic [[British people|British]] opponent, a superior spiritual power which would win out against the much more substantial, but merely worldly, advantages of the enemy.\u2019<ref name=\"Wilson1\"/>\n\nThe affair was soon reported in local and national newspapers, which caused more pilgrims to go to Tipperary, both to see the statues in Templemore and Walsh's cottage in Curraheen.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> On 31 August 1920 an RIC inspector wrote to the [[Dublin Castle administration]], estimating that over 15,000 pilgrims per day were coming down.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Papers dubbed Templemore as \u2018Pilgrimville\u2019 or \u2018Pilgrimtown\u2019.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> Many came seeking cures for various illnesses and reported that they had received them.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/><ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> One RIC officer resigned from his job to join a [[Religious order (Catholic)|religious order]].<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> One soldier is reported to converted to [[Catholic church|Catholicism]].<ref name=\"Wilson3\">{{cite book |last1=Wilson |first1=Ann |title=Kitsch, Enchantment and Power: The Bleeding Statues of Templemore. IN: Love Objects: Emotion, Design and Material Culture. |date=2014 |publisher=Bloomsbury Academic |page=95 |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=noXhAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n \nThe official position of the church was one of \u2018extreme reserve\u2019.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> The [[Parish in the Catholic Church|parish]] [[Priesthood in the Catholic Church|priest]] Reverend Kiely refused to see the statues.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> However, no effort was made to stop people making pilgrimages.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> Rev. Kiely commented \u2018If it is a prank, it will fizzle out, if not, why should I stop it?\u2019<ref name=\"IrishIndependent\">{{cite news |title=The miracle of the bleeding statues that halted an army |url=https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/the-miracle-of-the-bleeding-statues-that-halted-an-army-38693621.html |accessdate=11 April 2020 |publisher='The Irish Independent' |date=16 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nPrior to the apparitions beginning, Wilson had given a Virgin Mary statue to a local RIC constable named Thomas Winsey, according to the ''[[Tipperary Star]]''.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> Winsey placed the statue in the barracks.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> This too was said to be bleeding.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> One day a large crowd of pilgrims besieged the barracks and had to be physically restrained when they attempted to enter it.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> The statue was removed from the barracks.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> Police and military stopped appearing on the street shortly after.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/>\n\n==End==\n[[File:Michael Collins 1921.jpg|right|thumb|200px|Michael Collins in 1921]]The IRA effectively took over the area at this point.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> They kept order, organised traffic and helped pilgrims.<ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> However, they did not appear in the streets in uniform and there was an informal truce in effect between them and Crown forces.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/><ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> The local IRA commander [[James Leahy (republican)|James Leahy]] imposed a levy on traffic over the objections of the local [[Sinn F\u00e9in]] [[Teachta D\u00e1la|TD]].<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Donations were also raised from the pilgrims. The levy and donations had the effect of gaining a considerable amount for the IRA's war effort.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/>\n\nHowever, Leahy was concerned at the effect that tips given to IRA volunteers were having on discipline.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Himself and other local commanders interrogated Walsh and stopped believing him after this.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> He contacted IRA Director of Intelligence [[Michael Collins (Irish leader)|Michael Collins]].<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Collins had [[Dan Breen]] interrogate Walsh. Breen reported that Walsh \u2018was a fake\u2019.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/>  Collins sarcastically replied, \u2018One can\u2019t take any notice of what you say, Breen, because you have no religion\u2019.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/>\n\nHaving failed to get the church to intervene and denounce Walsh, Leahy and other IRA members decided to restart the war anyway.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> On 29 September, IRA volunteers attacked a group of RIC men between Templemore and Curraheen.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Two constables were killed.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> As anticipated, this brought police and army reinforcements to the area.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Soldiers looted and desecrated sites outside Templemore associated with the [[pilgrimage]].<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Rumours began that the town itself would soon be attacked.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Pilgrims fled the area.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> The statues apparently stopped bleeding.<ref name=\"Wilson3\"/>\n\nInterest in the statues and Walsh's cottage largely ended at this point, ending Templemore as a sight for pilgrimages.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Wilson3\"/> However, Michael Collins did receive a statue at his request.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> Upon receiving the statue, he smashed it.<ref name=\"IrishIndependent\"/> He discovered that inside was an [[alarm clock]] connected to fountain pen inserts containing sheep's blood.<ref name=\"IrishIndependent\"/> When the clock struck a certain time, it would send a spurt of blood out of the statue, given the impression it was bleeding.<ref name=\"IrishIndependent\"/> It is not clear that this statue performed in Templemore or was one of the ones owned by James Walsh.<ref name=\"Wilson3\"/> Collins had received complaints from a local priest that IRA volunteers had engineered statues that would bleed at intervals.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/>\n\nJames Walsh had been labelled as a possible spy by Dan Breen.<ref name=\"IrishIndependent\"/> At the request of Templemore clergy he was taken to [[Salesian school|Salesian College]] in [[County Limerick|Limerick]] and placed in the care of Father Aloysius Sutherland.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> He emigrated to [[Australia]] in 1923, settling in [[Sydney]].<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> Towards the end of his life he attempted to enter numerous religious orders but was unsuccessful due to a prior divorce.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> He died in Sydney in 1977, having never returned to Ireland.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/>\n\nThe affair is not well-known<ref name=\"thejournal.ie\">{{cite news |last1=Daly |first1=Susan |title=How holy \u2018apparitions\u2019 pressed pause on War of Independence |url=https://www.thejournal.ie/how-holy-apparitions-pressed-pause-on-war-of-independence-657793-Nov2012/#slide-slideshow1 |accessdate=11 April 2020 |publisher=thejournal.ie |date=4 November 2012}}</ref> despite gaining worldwide attention at the time.<ref name=\"Wilson3\"/> However, in November 2012 the Irish-language television broadcaster [[TG4]] screened a documentary about it.<ref name=\"thejournal.ie\"/> In 2019 the book ''The Templemore Miracles'', written by John Reynolds, was published.<ref name=\"Miracles1\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Knock Shrine]] - Alleged apparitions in [[Knock, County Mayo]] in 1879\n*[[Moving statues]] - Alleged apparitions in different parts of Ireland in 1985\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0E7lQt2L_ok] - Talk by John Reynolds, author of ''The Templemore Miracles''\n\n[[Category:1920 in Ireland]]\n[[Category:History of Catholicism in Ireland]]\n[[Category:History of County Tipperary]]\n[[Category:Irish War of Independence]]\n[[Category:Marian apparitions]]\n[[Category:Religion in County Tipperary]]\n[[Category:Templemore]]\n", "text_old": "In August and September 1920 the town of [[Templemore]] in [[County Tipperary]], [[Ireland]] was the sight of alleged [[Marian apparition|Marian apparitions]]. Thousands of people came to the town daily to see the apparitions.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\">{{cite journal |last1=Reynolds |first1=John |title=The Templemore miracles |journal=History Ireland |date=Jan/Feb 2009 |volume=17 |issue=1 |url=https://www.historyireland.com/20th-century-contemporary-history/the-templemore-miracles/ |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> The affair occurred during the [[Irish War of Independence]] and resulted in a short-lived local truce between the [[Irish Republican Army (1919-1922)|IRA]] and [[Crown forces]].<ref name=\"46MenDead\">{{cite book |last1=Reynolds |first1=John |title=46 Men Dead: The Royal Irish Constabulary in County Tipperary, 1919-22 |date=2016 |publisher=Gill & Macmillan Ltd |page=No page number given |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=OQiWDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> When the truce ended, [[pilgrim|pilgrims]] stopped coming to the town and the sightings ended. The affair is sometimes referred to as the '''Templemore miracles'''.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Miracles1\">{{cite book |last1=Reynolds |first1=John |title=The Templemore Miracles: Jimmy Walsh, Ceasefires and Moving Statues |date=2019 |publisher=The History Press}}</ref>\n\n==Apparitions==\nIn January 1919 the [[Irish War of Independence]] began. It would last until July 1921. On the night of 16 August 1920, [[British army|British soldiers]] of the [[Northamptonshire Regiment]] attacked Templemore in reprisal for the killing of an [[Royal Irish Constabulary|RIC]] officer by IRA volunteers earlier that day.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> They fired volleys and burned homes and businesses.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> No civilians or IRA men were killed but two soldiers died by accident in the fires.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/>\n\n[[File:Templemore Main Street and Town Hall, 2015.JPG|right|thumb|200px|Main Street including Town Hall in 2015]]Shortly after the attack, a sixteen-year old farm labourer named James Walsh claimed that he was visited by the [[Virgin Mary]] in his cottage in the nearby [[townland]] of Curraheen.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/><ref name=\"LittleBook\">{{cite book|last1=Blake |first1=Debbie |title=The Little Book of Tipperary |date=2018 |publisher=The History Press |page=No page given |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=K51ODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>She told him that she was troubled by what was happening in Ireland.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> At her request he dug a hole in the ground in his bedroom and this soon [[holy well|filled with spring water]].<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> Afterwards he claimed that all three statues of the Virgin Mary in his home [[weeping statue|began to bleed]].<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> He took these statues to Templemore, where the bleeding was witnessed.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/> One man who had been crippled for most of his life claimed he was dancing in the streets after seeing the staues. He was the first of many who claimed to have been cured of their ailments in the presence of Walsh or the statues.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/><ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Wilson1\">{{cite book |last1=Wilson |first1=Ann |title=Kitsch, Enchantment and Power: The Bleeding Statues of Templemore. IN: Love Objects: Emotion, Design and Material Culture. |date=2014 |publisher=Bloomsbury Academic |page=94 |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=noXhAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nLocals believed that divine intervention had prevented any of them being killed or wounded during the attack by the British.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> Walsh gathered people around the statues to say the [[rosary]] in [[Irish language|Irish]].<ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> According to Ann Wilson, the statues were seen \u2018as asserting the [[Irish Catholics|Catholic Irish]] identity of the population in the face of the non-Catholic [[British people|British]] opponent, a superior spiritual power which would win out against the much more substantial, but merely worldly, advantages of the enemy.\u2019<ref name=\"Wilson1\"/>\n\nThe affair was soon reported in local and national newspapers, which caused more pilgrims to go to Tipperary, both to see the statues in Templemore and Walsh\u2019s cottage in Curraheen.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> On 31 August 1920 an RIC inspector wrote to the [[Dublin Castle administration]], estimating that over 15,000 pilgrims per day were coming down.<ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/> Papers dubbed Templemore as \u2018Pilgrimville\u2019 or \u2018Pilgrimtown\u2019.<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> Many came seeking cures for various illnesses and reported that they had received them.<ref name=\"LittleBook\"/><ref name=\"HistoryIreland\"/><ref name=\"Wilson1\"/> One RIC officer resigned from his job to join a [[Religious order (Catholic)|religious order]].<ref name=\"46MenDead\"/> One soldier is reported to converted to [[Catholic church|Catholicism]].<ref name=\"Wilson2\">{{cite book |last1=Wilson |first1=Ann |title=Kitsch, Enchantment and Power: The Bleeding Statues of Templemore. IN: Love Objects: Emotion, Design and Material Culture. |date=2014 |publisher=Bloomsbury Academic |page=95 |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=noXhAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n \nThe official position of the church